\begin_layout Plain Layout
The METaL (Multimodal Experience Testbed and Laboratory) lab
\end_layout

\end_inset

 is a human-scale immersive environment for development of natural interaction
 techniques in virtual reality.
 This facility supports rapid development iteration and is comparable to
 virtual reality systems found in industry.
 Integration of haptic force-feedback with visual display, audio effects,
 and physical simulation permits the creation of multimodal experiences.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
METaL consists of:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Two walls and the floor of a 12'x9'x9' (4m x 3m x 3m) space.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
An ART TrackPack 4 system tracks the position and orientation of a user's
 head, wand, and other objects in the space.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Computational resources are provided by a head node, with graphics on all
 walls generated by a render node.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Each of these two nodes is a rack-mounted server (running either Red Hat
 Enterprise Linux 6 or Windows XP x64) containing:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Dual Intel Xeon X5677 quad-core processors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
24 GB of RAM.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A Creative Sound Blaster X-Fi Titanium sound card.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The head node contains an NVIDIA Quadro FX 5800 card to power a 24" LCD
 display.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The render node connects to two NVIDIA Quadro Plex 2200-D2 visual computing
 systems, each of which contains two NVIDIA Quadro FX 5800 cards and an
 NVIDIA G-Sync II card to provide framelocked rendering of active stereo
 graphics.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The three Digital Projection International TiTAN WUXGA-3D projectors display
 active stereo at 1600x1200x1200 pixels each, producing 5.28 megapixels across
 297
\begin_inset space \thinspace{}
\end_inset

sq.
\begin_inset space \thinspace{}
\end_inset

ft.
 (33
\begin_inset space \thinspace{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{m}^{2}$
\end_inset

) of display surfaces.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Surround audio generated by either node is transferred over a digital optical
 link to a Yamaha RX-V367 receiver and played over a 5.1 surround sound system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
One gigabit Ethernet switch is dedicated to system control, tracking data,
 and internal communication, while a second gigabit Ethernet switch provides
 both nodes with a high-speed connection to other ISU and VRAC resources
 and the Internet.
\end_layout

